setTreeLevel

public void setTreeLevel(java.util.Map treeLevel)
Setter for JSF Managed Property "treeLevel". The treeLevel map is configured in the faces-config.xml file to have the following (viewdef,facetname) key/value pairs: 1. ( key="oracle.apps.fnd.appltest.diagfwk.ui.model.view.TagNameVO"", value="TagNameNode") 2. ( key="oracle.apps.fnd.appltest.diagfwk.ui.model.view.TagValueVO"", value="TagValueNode") 3. ( key="oracle.apps.fnd.appltest.diagfwk.ui.model.view.TagNameToTestVO"", value="TestNode")

Parameters:
treeLevel - map of (viewdef,facetname) pairs

getTreeLevel

public java.util.Map getTreeLevel()
Getter for JSF Managed Property "treeLevel". This property defines a Map of (key,value) pairs used by the af:switcher tag in the Example page to switch the facet to display based on the fully-qualified name of the view object whose data is represented by a given tree node. The af:switcher tag has its facetName property set to the following EL expression: #{Example.treeLevel[node.hierType.viewDefName]}

Returns:
map of (viewdef,facetname) pairs
